events.name: Boston Celtics at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram highlighted a 31-point performance by hitting a go-ahead 3-pointer with 33.3 seconds left in overtime, and the New Orleans Pelicans held on for 120-115 victory over the Boston Celtics on Sunday after rallying from 24 points down in...
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans rally from 24 down, top Celtics 120-115 in overtime

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 31 points and nine assists as the Oklahoma City Thunder beat Cleveland 117-101 on Sunday night, handing the Cavaliers their 10th consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oklahoma City deals Cavaliers 10th straight loss, 117-101

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 37 points and 11 rebounds, Evan Fournier added a season-high 29 points and the Orlando Magic beat the Detroit Pistons 105-96 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Vucevic scores 37 points, Magic beat Pistons 105-96

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam and Fred VanVleet each had 23 points and the Toronto Raptors beat the Philadelphia 76ers 110-103 for their fourth straight victory Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors turn back 76ers 110-103 for 4th straight win

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 25 points and 14 rebounds, helping the New York Knicks recover after blowing a 21-point lead and beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 103-99 on Sunday night, giving Tom Thibodeau a win over the team he last coached.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks blow big lead but give Thibodeau win over Wolves

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 35 points and 15 assists, Clint Capela added 22 points and 10 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Denver Nuggets 123-115 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young, Clint Capela boost Hawks past Nuggets 123-115

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 37 points and the Brooklyn Nets held off a furious fourth-quarter rally to edge the Los Angeles Clippers 112-108 on Sunday night for their season-best sixth victory in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets hold on to edge Clippers, win season-best 6th in a row

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 38 points and Khris Middleton scored 32 to lead the Milwaukee Bucks past the skidding Sacramento Kings 128-115 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo, Middleton lead Bucks past Kings 128-115
